---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const focusAreas = [
  {
    title: 'Security operations & incident readiness',
    text: 'Practical support for triage, investigation workflows, response planning, and the operating habits that make incidents easier to understand and contain.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Detection engineering & automation',
    text: 'Focused improvements to detections, enrichment, alert handling, and repeatable automation—with attention to failure modes and maintainability.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Applied AI for security work',
    text: 'Careful use of AI to summarize, prioritize, and accelerate security workflows without hiding assumptions or removing human judgment.',
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Services | VORASEC"
  description="Developing cybersecurity services informed by hands-on security operations, incident response, automation, and applied AI."
>
  <section class="hero shell services-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">VORASEC services · In development</p>
    <h1>Practical security work, built around useful outcomes.</h1>
    <p>
      VORASEC will be the home for independent cybersecurity services shaped by
      my experience in security operations, incident response, automation, and
      applied AI. The offering is still taking form; this page marks the
      direction, not a finished catalog.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section shell" aria-labelledby="focus-heading">
    <p class="eyebrow">Planned focus</p>
    <h2 id="focus-heading">Where I expect to help.</h2>
    <div class="services-grid">
      {focusAreas.map((area) => (
        <article>
          <h3>{area.title}</h3>
          <p>{area.text}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section shell principles">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Working principles</p>
      <h2>Clear scope. Visible reasoning. Durable handoff.</h2>
    </div>
    <p>
      Any future engagement should leave the work more understandable than it
      was before: documented decisions, bounded automation, observable failure,
      and recommendations that fit the environment rather than a generic playbook.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section shell early-note">
    <p class="eyebrow">Early conversations</p>
    <h2>The services are evolving alongside the work.</h2>
    <p>
      I’m not presenting a polished consultancy menu yet. For now, this is a
      signal of intent and a place to build the offering deliberately.
    </p>
    <a class="button primary" href="/about">Learn more about me</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .services-hero {
    position: relative;
    max-width: 1000px;
  }

  .services-hero::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    right: 0;
    bottom: 3rem;
    width: min(28vw, 250px);
    aspect-ratio: 1;
    background: url('/favicon.png') center / contain no-repeat;
    opacity: 0.08;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .services-hero h1,
  .services-hero > p {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .services-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 2.5rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .services-grid article {
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .principles {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.25fr 0.75fr;
    gap: 5rem;
    align-items: end;
  }

  .principles > p {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .early-note {
    max-width: 780px;
    margin-left: max(1.25rem, calc((100vw - var(--max)) / 2));
  }

  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .services-hero::after {
      width: 8rem;
      bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .services-grid,
    .principles {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
